\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Compatibilities vs incompatibilities}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Which incompatabilities are long term dealbreakers.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Emotional intimacy when one person wants to do more emotional processing.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 you're either all in your current relationship or it's taking away from both of you. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 I was\~}{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 not}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \~expecting the the insane flood of monkey-brained love chemicals that hit me like an 18-wheeler the next morning. It felt like my entire nervous system had been hijacked; it was somehow intoxicatingly wonderful, and also pants-shittingly terrifying, nauseating and agonizing all at once. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 When I told my friends that I felt like I'd lost my mind, they just laughed. The general response was:\~}{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 "Yep, that's how it's supposed to feel. Welcome to being human. Sucks, doesn't it? It's also great. Congratulations!"}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 If everyone orients their lives around fleeting romantic intensity, then the village will descend into chaos.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Temper this passionate thing that lives inside humans. In ancient cultures.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Children are negatively affected when one or both parents are destabilized by romantic obsession.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Pair bonding is purpose and stability.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 This dream that we can maintain this elevated euphoric love state for a long period of time. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Discipline, Stability, consistency, service to others as core aspects of long term relationships. But people don\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t orient their lives around that. They want their heroin. The euphoric highpoint. That is unstable. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 These people tend to be unhappy.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 This passionate euphoric high is something they should be expecting and they shouldn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t settle for anything less; around their children, she is chasing this thing, that the child can\u8217\'92t give, so the child suppresses emotional needs.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Wonder how it is that anyone accomplishes anything when this feeling exists.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \fi720\sl288\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 And it wasn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t only blood, it was her very being which dripped down his grasping fingers, such that with each passing moment he was holding less of her and more her bag of bones. She was made of little else. So stark was this feeling that he could scarcely believe that she\u8217\'92d ever stood up on two feet, much less been a person who could speak.}}